\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Accuracy--throughput frontier. Flat baselines occupy fixed points~(throughput independent of traffic mix). TRIAGE's operating point depends on the deployment attack rate~$r$: at the balanced test-set rate~($r{\approx }50\,\%$, lowest star) it is competitive with flat models; as $r$ decreases toward production levels~($r{\leq }5\,\%$), TRIAGE moves upward into a region no flat classifier can reach---combining high accuracy with high throughput because most flows exit after Stage~1. Throughput is computed analytically from per-stage latencies via Eq.~\eqref  {eq:throughput}.}}{6}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pareto}{{2}{6}{}{figure.2}{}}
